Starting Monday, 4/6, NJ students in grades 3-6 can tune into public television to follow some of the classroom lessons they've been missing since the closure of school.
Teachers will be providing lessons on NJTV, the state's public access network, as well archived on the network's website, NJTVonline.org, in an initiative designed to advance remote instruction at home. NJTV, the NJEA, and the NJ DOE partnered together in the effort.
The lessons will be available during four programs on the show NJTV Learning Live each weekday.
3rd Grade instruction begins at 9 a.m.;
4th Grade instruction begins at 10 a.m.;
5th Grade instruction begins at 11 a.m.;
6th Grade instruction begins at 12 p.m.

